This paper focuses on evaluating different approaches for visualizing temporal event sequences, which is a topic that falls under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and visualization (cs.VIS). The paper also discusses techniques for coping with data volume and variety, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
